1
00:00:00,050 --> 00:00:02,269
[Previously]
There will be another teacher to replace you.

2
00:00:02,270 --> 00:00:04,109
Do you have to go this far?

3
00:00:04,110 --> 00:00:11,710
Do you know what's much harder than apologizing?

4
00:00:12,410 --> 00:00:16,200
It's forgiveness.

5
00:00:16,200 --> 00:00:20,200
Especially learning to forgive yourself.

6
00:00:20,210 --> 00:00:22,369
I know you have done your best.

7
00:00:22,370 --> 00:00:26,389
And I know that Torfun could see this and forgive you.

8
00:00:26,390 --> 00:00:28,029
Will you forget me?

9
00:00:28,030 --> 00:00:30,489
Tian, I will never forget you.

10
00:00:30,490 --> 00:00:32,830
Not even for a single day.

11
00:00:45,330 --> 00:00:51,710
[The first day in Pha Pun Dao]

12
00:03:21,090 --> 00:03:23,389
[1. Tie the net to all four corners.
2. Ward off mosquitoes with the pillow.
3. Tug the edges of the net under the mattress.]

13
00:03:23,389 --> 00:03:25,290
[Be careful! That's hot!]

14
00:05:11,890 --> 00:05:21,123
[Chapter 10]

15
00:05:49,990 --> 00:05:56,430
♫ The story that's been told however many times is still the same ♫

16
00:05:56,430 --> 00:06:02,950
♫ It's that I love you, love you. It has never changed ♫

17
00:06:02,950 --> 00:06:09,350
♫ If perhaps the stars hear the words of the prayers within my heart ♫

18
00:06:09,350 --> 00:06:21,060
♫ No matter how many thousands of times, I'll still ask for my heart to be near you ♫

19
00:06:21,060 --> 00:06:25,080
[A Tale of Thousand Stars]

20
00:06:49,070 --> 00:06:51,030
All right, Kalae.

21
00:06:52,390 --> 00:06:55,169
That's fried chicken and sticky rice, made by me and Khao Neung,

22
00:06:55,169 --> 00:06:57,770
for you, in case you get hungry.

23
00:07:00,690 --> 00:07:02,410
Thank you.

24
00:07:03,190 --> 00:07:04,940
Can I have a hug?

25
00:07:21,030 --> 00:07:25,689
I knitted this all by myself. Grandma taught me how to knit it.

26
00:07:25,689 --> 00:07:27,523
Thank you.

27
00:07:42,130 --> 00:07:46,250
I drew this with you and me here.

28
00:07:47,130 --> 00:07:51,769
My father said you were our family, too.

29
00:07:51,769 --> 00:07:53,770
Thank you, Ayi.

30
00:08:05,570 --> 00:08:08,009
Meejoo, come here.

31
00:08:08,010 --> 00:08:10,449
We have talked about this, right?

32
00:08:10,450 --> 00:08:13,890
We won't make it hard for him.

33
00:08:14,490 --> 00:08:19,430
Mr. Seetian, I know now what I want to be, when I grow up.

34
00:08:22,330 --> 00:08:23,849
What do you want to be, Meejoo?

35
00:08:23,850 --> 00:08:26,510
I want to be a teacher like Mr. Seetian.

36
00:08:27,610 --> 00:08:29,390
Well then,

37
00:08:30,490 --> 00:08:33,409
can you check everyone's homework for me?

38
00:08:33,410 --> 00:08:35,350
Of course.

39
00:08:37,130 --> 00:08:39,170
Very good.

40
00:08:41,470 --> 00:08:44,870
When a teacher has to leave,

41
00:08:44,870 --> 00:08:48,350
the kids are always acting like this.

42
00:08:48,870 --> 00:08:52,269
But this is the first time,

43
00:08:52,270 --> 00:08:56,490
not only the kids are sad,

44
00:08:57,710 --> 00:09:03,170
but the villagers don't want to see you leave either.

45
00:09:05,030 --> 00:09:10,669
Anyway, when you feel like having traditional northern food,

46
00:09:10,670 --> 00:09:13,109
please think of this place.

47
00:09:13,110 --> 00:09:16,569
You are always welcome here.

48
00:09:16,570 --> 00:09:19,109
It would be great if you tell us in advance, though,

49
00:09:19,110 --> 00:09:22,110
so I can prepare an omelet for you.

50
00:09:27,630 --> 00:09:29,870
Thank you so much, Khama.

51
00:09:32,450 --> 00:09:34,620
This shirt

52
00:09:35,810 --> 00:09:39,170
may not be as good as your designer clothes.

53
00:09:42,310 --> 00:09:46,910
On the contrary, this one is priceless.

54
00:09:47,590 --> 00:09:49,990
Don't forget that we dodged a bullet together.

55
00:09:56,190 --> 00:09:57,870
Thank you, Phi.

56
00:09:58,470 --> 00:10:00,103
Thank you.

57
00:10:18,090 --> 00:10:20,240
If you are looking for the chief,

58
00:10:21,570 --> 00:10:23,920
I haven't seen him since this morning.

59
00:10:44,410 --> 00:10:45,549
P'Yod.

60
00:10:45,550 --> 00:10:48,550
Yes, it's me.

61
00:10:49,650 --> 00:10:51,490
The chief is busy,

62
00:10:51,990 --> 00:10:55,650
so he asked me to send you off.

63
00:10:57,170 --> 00:10:59,390
Good luck, Mr. Tian.

64
00:11:03,650 --> 00:11:06,570
Chief Phupha wants you to keep this.

65
00:11:08,970 --> 00:11:14,490
[A Tale of Thousand Stars]

66
00:11:26,910 --> 00:11:28,509
Thank you, P'Yod.

67
00:11:28,510 --> 00:11:30,450
You're welcome.

68
00:11:36,030 --> 00:11:38,109
All right, everyone.

69
00:11:38,110 --> 00:11:39,729
Let's take a picture together.

70
00:11:39,730 --> 00:11:41,649
Let me hold that for you.

71
00:11:41,650 --> 00:11:45,150
Come and take a picture with Mr. Tian.

72
00:11:49,350 --> 00:11:53,870
Here we go. One, two, three!

73
00:11:53,870 --> 00:11:56,700
- See? Let's take some pictures.
- Yes, yes, yes.

74
00:11:56,700 --> 00:11:57,989
Let's pose lively!

75
00:11:57,990 --> 00:12:02,750
One, two, three, hey!

76
00:12:09,070 --> 00:12:12,349
Everyone, let's have a big group hug.

77
00:12:12,349 --> 00:12:14,950
Go, ahead.

78
00:12:43,450 --> 00:12:45,150
All right, kids.

79
00:12:46,010 --> 00:12:48,869
His van is here.

80
00:12:48,870 --> 00:12:51,030
Mr. Tian has to go now.

81
00:13:04,590 --> 00:13:06,390
Bye-bye, Phi.

82
00:13:07,330 --> 00:13:09,309
Good luck, Mr. Tian.

83
00:13:09,309 --> 00:13:11,890
Travel safely, Phi Seetian.

84
00:13:11,890 --> 00:13:14,610
Visit us sometime.

85
00:14:17,710 --> 00:14:19,490
If there's a miracle
[Here's the meaning of Torfun's wish.]

86
00:14:19,490 --> 00:14:23,309
on the last day of the year, if I finish counting to one thousand stars,

87
00:14:23,310 --> 00:14:26,929
I'll wish for the Green Giant, who has been closing off his heart,

88
00:14:26,930 --> 00:14:29,209
to meet someone who can soften his heart,

89
00:14:29,210 --> 00:14:31,649
so that he opens up his heart

90
00:14:31,650 --> 00:14:36,010
and loves that someone wholeheartedly.

91
00:15:10,610 --> 00:15:16,129
It doesn't matter that you didn't finish counting to one thousand stars that night.

92
00:15:16,130 --> 00:15:21,130
At the end of the day, you have already made Torfun's wish come true.

93
00:15:29,830 --> 00:15:35,230
Tian, I would like our tale to end here.

94
00:15:35,710 --> 00:15:38,460
It's the best ending we could have.

95
00:15:38,460 --> 00:15:42,110
You don't owe us anything.

96
00:15:42,110 --> 00:15:47,370
From now on, I want you to put everything here behind

97
00:15:47,370 --> 00:15:49,789
and go back to your own life.

98
00:15:49,790 --> 00:15:55,470
Do what your heart wants and start over for your own sake.

99
00:15:56,490 --> 00:15:58,849
I wish you all the best.

100
00:15:58,849 --> 00:16:00,950
[I wish you all the best. - Phupha]

101
00:16:25,350 --> 00:16:28,010
I will always be with you.
[Heart of Phupha]

102
00:17:30,770 --> 00:17:36,429
Dear Chief, it's been weeks since I came back home.

103
00:17:36,430 --> 00:17:39,169
My life here is totally opposite,

104
00:17:39,170 --> 00:17:44,890
which makes it harder to believe that I dared to live up there by myself.

105
00:17:47,590 --> 00:17:51,049
Here, I don't have to set up a mosquito net,

106
00:17:51,050 --> 00:17:54,110
and I have a maid who makes the bed for me.

107
00:17:56,690 --> 00:17:59,529
When I want to eat something, I can just ask for it,

108
00:17:59,530 --> 00:18:02,630
and don't need to waste time on starting a fire.

109
00:18:06,550 --> 00:18:13,010
Each day, I can live quietly without any kids around.

110
00:18:19,150 --> 00:18:21,210
- Auntie.
- Yes?

111
00:18:21,210 --> 00:18:22,809
Can you send out this letter for me?

112
00:18:22,810 --> 00:18:24,670
Sure.

113
00:18:27,770 --> 00:18:29,869
And most importantly,

114
00:18:29,870 --> 00:18:35,940
I have no grouchy giant around to keep his eye on me, even when I'm having a bath.

115
00:18:35,940 --> 00:18:39,560
[Jula's Herb | Watermelon Aura Soap]

116
00:19:01,150 --> 00:19:03,950
This is pretty much my life.

117
00:19:03,950 --> 00:19:08,210
I'm living a life for my own sake, just like you told me to.

118
00:19:13,030 --> 00:19:19,470
Somehow, I miss the difficult life up there in the village.

119
00:19:38,630 --> 00:19:41,089
Auntie, is there a letter for me?

120
00:19:41,089 --> 00:19:43,189
Wait a moment.

121
00:19:43,189 --> 00:19:45,150
You can give them all to me.

122
00:19:52,610 --> 00:19:54,370
Thank you.

123
00:20:13,030 --> 00:20:17,829
This sour pork is called Jinsom and this spicy minced pork is called Laab Khua.

124
00:20:17,830 --> 00:20:19,929
And this is Jack Fruit Salad.

125
00:20:19,930 --> 00:20:20,989
All right.

126
00:20:20,990 --> 00:20:22,330
What about this? Is this steamed curry?

127
00:20:22,330 --> 00:20:25,969
No, this is called Ab Ong Aor.

128
00:20:25,970 --> 00:20:28,889
- Ab Ong Aor?
- Yes, try it. It's yummy.

129
00:20:28,889 --> 00:20:30,089
What is it?

130
00:20:30,090 --> 00:20:31,769
Pig brain.

131
00:20:31,770 --> 00:20:34,129
What? Okay.

132
00:20:34,130 --> 00:20:35,909
Try it. Trust me, it's good.

133
00:20:35,910 --> 00:20:39,249
No, thanks. I think I'm still not used to this.

134
00:20:39,250 --> 00:20:44,409
You changed from a fancy restaurant to a northern Thai food restaurant.

135
00:20:44,410 --> 00:20:46,209
I was there for several months,

136
00:20:46,210 --> 00:20:48,569
so isn't it normal that I'd miss the local food from up there?

137
00:20:48,570 --> 00:20:50,609
Really?

138
00:20:50,610 --> 00:20:53,969
Is it the food there or someone in particular?

139
00:20:53,970 --> 00:20:55,729
Definitely the food!

140
00:20:55,730 --> 00:20:57,009
I can swear on it, if you want me to.

141
00:20:57,010 --> 00:20:58,289
Go ahead.

142
00:20:58,289 --> 00:20:59,950
Swear!

143
00:21:03,350 --> 00:21:05,189
He sneezed.

144
00:21:05,190 --> 00:21:07,530
Someone must be thinking of him.

145
00:21:09,130 --> 00:21:10,929
My nose is itchy.

146
00:21:10,930 --> 00:21:13,769
Mind yourself. You'll get married soon,

147
00:21:13,770 --> 00:21:14,949
so stop fooling around in town.

148
00:21:14,950 --> 00:21:17,049
What are you talking about?

149
00:21:17,050 --> 00:21:19,750
I went there to find my wedding gifts.

150
00:21:20,810 --> 00:21:22,930
Is the Ab Ong Aor ready?

151
00:21:23,710 --> 00:21:25,049
It's still hot.

152
00:21:25,050 --> 00:21:27,069
Wow, we're having Ab Ong Aor today?

153
00:21:27,069 --> 00:21:29,609
Yes, we do.

154
00:21:29,610 --> 00:21:32,029
Ab Ong Aor.

155
00:21:32,030 --> 00:21:37,889
I can't help thinking of Mr. Tian when I see Ab Ong Aor.

156
00:21:37,890 --> 00:21:40,969
It's his favorite dish.

157
00:21:40,970 --> 00:21:43,829
He was reluctant to have it in the beginning,

158
00:21:43,830 --> 00:21:47,380
but later on he finished all of it by himself every time.

159
00:21:55,770 --> 00:21:59,030
It's still hot, so be careful.

160
00:22:06,450 --> 00:22:10,469
There you are! Are you sure you're not thinking of someone?

161
00:22:10,470 --> 00:22:12,850
I'm thinking about work. Damn it, Doc!

162
00:22:12,850 --> 00:22:16,989
Why are you thinking of work here?

163
00:22:16,990 --> 00:22:19,289
Mr. Sakda got caught already.

164
00:22:19,290 --> 00:22:21,109
I don't think it's that.

165
00:22:21,109 --> 00:22:26,429
You must be thinking of someone who likes… Ab Ong Aor.

166
00:22:26,429 --> 00:22:28,310
Come on, Khama.

167
00:22:29,670 --> 00:22:32,580
So, what's next?

168
00:22:32,580 --> 00:22:34,509
We can just go home. You're done here, right?

169
00:22:34,509 --> 00:22:36,899
Not this. I meant your life.

170
00:22:36,900 --> 00:22:38,399
What are you going to do next?

171
00:22:38,400 --> 00:22:40,329
Do you want to just stay at home?

172
00:22:40,330 --> 00:22:42,539
Don't you think it's time to move on or something?

173
00:22:42,539 --> 00:22:44,349
I don't know.

174
00:22:44,350 --> 00:22:46,399
What else do you think I should do?

175
00:22:46,400 --> 00:22:48,529
Do whatever you want to.

176
00:22:48,530 --> 00:22:50,710
You have time now.

177
00:22:54,840 --> 00:22:57,269
I used to think that I didn't have much time left,

178
00:22:57,270 --> 00:23:02,780
so I never thought about what I'd like to do or what I'd want.

179
00:23:03,760 --> 00:23:05,889
When I was in the village,

180
00:23:05,890 --> 00:23:08,499
I found my happiness there,

181
00:23:08,500 --> 00:23:11,489
but my parents eventually dragged me down here

182
00:23:11,489 --> 00:23:14,449
and told me, that that life wasn't for me.

183
00:23:14,450 --> 00:23:18,390
So I really don't know what I should do next.

184
00:23:18,390 --> 00:23:20,319
Well, then,

185
00:23:20,320 --> 00:23:24,720
I think you can just go back to college and finish that.

186
00:23:24,720 --> 00:23:27,509
Did my mother tell you to convince me?

187
00:23:27,510 --> 00:23:28,809
Your mother is worried about you

188
00:23:28,810 --> 00:23:30,219
and she wants you to complete your degree.

189
00:23:30,219 --> 00:23:33,620
Don't you think I'd know that I should finish my degree?

190
00:23:34,280 --> 00:23:38,609
I'm just not sure whether I want to continue with engineering.

191
00:23:38,610 --> 00:23:40,143
Why?

192
00:23:40,810 --> 00:23:43,859
I chose engineering because of my mother.

193
00:23:43,860 --> 00:23:46,530
What? What the hell?

194
00:23:47,630 --> 00:23:49,430
You are so damn strange.

195
00:23:52,120 --> 00:23:57,369
Sometimes you don't know what you really want

196
00:23:57,370 --> 00:24:00,490
until you try it.

197
00:24:00,490 --> 00:24:04,670
That's how you know if it's right for you or not.

198
00:24:06,340 --> 00:24:08,370
Then answer me this.

199
00:24:09,130 --> 00:24:11,480
What do you think is right for you?

200
00:24:15,920 --> 00:24:17,790
I don't know either,

201
00:24:18,790 --> 00:24:21,950
but definitely not engineering.

202
00:24:22,890 --> 00:24:26,779
Seriously, just get it done. No need to think too much about it.

203
00:24:26,779 --> 00:24:31,249
In the end, we have to take over our family's business anyway.

204
00:24:31,250 --> 00:24:33,150
You're thinking too much about it.

205
00:24:42,440 --> 00:24:43,869
- Ai Tul.
- Yes?

206
00:24:43,870 --> 00:24:47,589
Before going home, could you drop me off somewhere?

207
00:24:47,589 --> 00:24:51,900
[Sangthong Aid Foundation]

208
00:24:52,670 --> 00:24:54,470
Good evening, Sir.

209
00:24:56,100 --> 00:24:57,639
We are closed today.

210
00:24:57,640 --> 00:24:59,690
Can you come again on Monday?

211
00:25:00,340 --> 00:25:02,073
It's me, Sir.

212
00:25:02,900 --> 00:25:04,079
Hello, Tian.

213
00:25:04,080 --> 00:25:05,389
Good evening, Sir.

214
00:25:05,390 --> 00:25:08,580
- Hello, hello.
- This is my souvenir from Pha Pun Dao.

215
00:25:09,040 --> 00:25:11,559
Thank you. How are you doing?

216
00:25:11,560 --> 00:25:13,409
I'm doing fine. What about you?

217
00:25:13,409 --> 00:25:15,143
I'm fine.

218
00:25:22,650 --> 00:25:25,169
This tea is from Pha Pun Dao village.

219
00:25:25,170 --> 00:25:29,929
I helped the villagers harvest the tea leaves and I can guarantee that it's chemical free.

220
00:25:29,930 --> 00:25:31,929
It's aromatic.

221
00:25:31,929 --> 00:25:34,240
Very nice.

222
00:25:38,640 --> 00:25:40,390
How were you doing there?

223
00:25:40,920 --> 00:25:45,030
Did you manage to find the thing you were looking for up there?

224
00:25:46,470 --> 00:25:48,879
I'm not sure.

225
00:25:48,880 --> 00:25:54,589
At first, I thought there would be something I could give them there.

226
00:25:54,589 --> 00:25:59,150
In the end, it was me who got something from them.

227
00:25:59,750 --> 00:26:03,160
Maybe it was Torfun, who wanted you to get that.

228
00:26:07,000 --> 00:26:08,930
Before this,

229
00:26:08,930 --> 00:26:14,250
I was only thinking about what I could do to repay Torfun.

230
00:26:15,040 --> 00:26:18,809
Now that I got everything done,

231
00:26:18,809 --> 00:26:22,170
I don't know what I should do next.

232
00:26:23,230 --> 00:26:24,599
What to do next?

233
00:26:24,600 --> 00:26:28,119
This is the million-dollar question to young people these days,

234
00:26:28,120 --> 00:26:32,779
and most of the time, they would say that they want to follow their passion.

235
00:26:35,220 --> 00:26:36,920
Isn't that a way to do things?

236
00:26:39,320 --> 00:26:41,870
If we could only follow our passion

237
00:26:42,550 --> 00:26:46,050
and do what we love to do,

238
00:26:46,050 --> 00:26:51,419
then I should only be staying home instead of breaking my back while gardening.

239
00:26:54,280 --> 00:26:55,889
You've got a point there.

240
00:26:55,890 --> 00:26:57,339
Look.

241
00:26:57,339 --> 00:26:59,380
See that plant?

242
00:27:03,280 --> 00:27:05,539
Isn't it the one I helped you with the other day?

243
00:27:05,540 --> 00:27:07,273
Yes.

244
00:27:07,273 --> 00:27:10,469
At first, I was afraid that it would be too hot for it in the sun,

245
00:27:10,470 --> 00:27:15,040
so I moved it to the shade, but it withered.

246
00:27:15,040 --> 00:27:18,149
So I moved it back to get both the sun and the rain,

247
00:27:18,150 --> 00:27:22,700
and after that, it's constantly blooming beautifully.

248
00:27:26,740 --> 00:27:31,549
Sometimes, you just need to find a place that fits you.

249
00:27:32,410 --> 00:27:36,580
How do I know which place fits me the best?

250
00:27:37,410 --> 00:27:39,989
There, look over there.

251
00:27:39,990 --> 00:27:44,560
The place that fits you will make you grow.

252
00:27:57,240 --> 00:27:58,673
Mom,

253
00:27:59,720 --> 00:28:01,790
I have made up my mind.

254
00:28:04,130 --> 00:28:06,130
I will go back to studying.

255
00:28:07,130 --> 00:28:08,399
Really?

256
00:28:08,400 --> 00:28:10,599
Then let's get you a new car tomorrow,

257
00:28:10,600 --> 00:28:12,429
since you'll need a car to drive to your college.

258
00:28:12,430 --> 00:28:15,399
But I don't want to study engineering now.

259
00:28:15,400 --> 00:28:17,649
Oh, why?

260
00:28:17,649 --> 00:28:21,450
I want to study something that can help people.

261
00:28:23,030 --> 00:28:27,049
How about med school then?

262
00:28:27,050 --> 00:28:30,200
I'm not smart enough to study at med school.

263
00:28:30,200 --> 00:28:31,813
Mom,

264
00:28:33,160 --> 00:28:35,360
I want to study to become a teacher.

265
00:28:36,410 --> 00:28:37,539
Tian,

266
00:28:37,540 --> 00:28:40,690
do you still think about that?

267
00:28:41,200 --> 00:28:43,789
Why do I have to stop thinking about it?

268
00:28:43,790 --> 00:28:50,610
I just realized that teaching kids makes me so happy.

269
00:28:53,360 --> 00:28:58,989
Tian, but studying education is not as fun as what you experienced up there.

270
00:28:58,990 --> 00:29:02,419
What I experienced up there wasn't that fun either, Mom.

271
00:29:02,420 --> 00:29:04,989
Why does everyone think that it was a fun thing?

272
00:29:04,990 --> 00:29:07,809
I know very well that it's difficult.

273
00:29:07,810 --> 00:29:09,439
So?

274
00:29:09,440 --> 00:29:12,149
If you know it's difficult, why do you want to study it?

275
00:29:12,150 --> 00:29:13,509
Why don't you choose something that─

276
00:29:13,509 --> 00:29:15,759
That you can show off to other people, right?

277
00:29:15,760 --> 00:29:16,879
Tian.

278
00:29:16,880 --> 00:29:18,399
Isn't it true?

279
00:29:18,400 --> 00:29:20,819
Being born into the Sophaditsakul family,

280
00:29:20,820 --> 00:29:24,070
I must take my family's reputation into account in whatever I do.

281
00:29:29,180 --> 00:29:31,010
All this time,

282
00:29:31,710 --> 00:29:34,179
I've been doing everything you wanted me to.

283
00:29:34,180 --> 00:29:36,030
But this time,

284
00:29:37,360 --> 00:29:40,060
can't you let me do what I want, just for once?

285
00:29:55,690 --> 00:29:58,489
Nong Tian, would you like cooked rice or rice porridge?

286
00:29:58,489 --> 00:30:00,809
No, thanks, I'll have it outside.

287
00:30:00,810 --> 00:30:02,589
Eat your breakfast here.

288
00:30:02,589 --> 00:30:05,040
We have something to talk to you about.

289
00:30:08,010 --> 00:30:09,689
I'll have rice, then.

290
00:30:09,689 --> 00:30:11,223
Here you are.

291
00:30:19,050 --> 00:30:22,669
Your mother and I have talked.

292
00:30:22,670 --> 00:30:25,370
She agreed to let you study education.

293
00:30:25,910 --> 00:30:27,619
Really?

294
00:30:27,620 --> 00:30:29,710
Thank you, Mom.

295
00:30:33,000 --> 00:30:35,660
I want you to study here.

296
00:30:40,030 --> 00:30:41,439
In the USA?

297
00:30:41,439 --> 00:30:45,569
Yes, even though I don't want to be away from you,

298
00:30:45,570 --> 00:30:48,209
but this institution is known for their education degrees.

299
00:30:48,210 --> 00:30:51,840
Many of my friends' kids couldn't get into this place.

300
00:30:52,570 --> 00:30:58,409
But Mom, there are many good institutions here in Thailand. I think─

301
00:30:58,409 --> 00:31:02,659
Tian, your mother already agreed to let you study education.

302
00:31:02,660 --> 00:31:04,810
For this matter,

303
00:31:05,560 --> 00:31:07,690
